<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871028-0048 </DOCNO><HL> Defense Contracts Are Awarded</HL><DD> 10/28/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> LOR UIS ROKDEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   A total of $61.8 million in defense contracts have been awarded to three companies.    Loral Corp., New York, said it was given $35.6 million in contracts for equipment and logistics support for Army and Air Force training programs.    Blue Bell, Pa.-based Unisys Corp. was issued a $14.7 million Navy contract to integrate combat systems on a guided-missile frigate.    And Pittsburgh-based Rockwell International Corp. was given an $11.5 million Army contract for Hellfire missile improvements. </TEXT></DOC>